    "body": "#851 now includes these tests, which check for the reaction to an invalid opcode in a bunch of contexts: https://github.com/ethereum/tests/blob/84d42b6f6b757b6f0cde4d812db0569c76245c8a/src/GeneralStateTestsFiller/stBadOpcode/manyContextsFiller.yml\r\n\r\nThe next version of solidity (0.8.5) will have in Yul a `verbatim` function that lets us specify arbitrary machine language code. I think we should leave this issue open until that's the official version, and then I'll add invalid opcodes to Yul other than as `invalid()`, which translates to 0xFE.",
